Goldman Sachs Fined $10 Million; Will Halt the ’Huddles’

-- B y   B i l l   K o e n i g
-- 
2011-06-09T14:28:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/goldman-to-halt-huddles-between-analysts-traders-after-10-million-fine.html
Massachusetts Secretary of the
Commonwealth William Galvin’s office said  Goldman Sachs Group
Inc. (GS)  was fined $10 million in a settlement.  Galvin’s office also said in an e-mailed statement that
Goldman agreed to halt internal meetings among equity research
analysts and traders known as “huddles.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Koenig at 
 wkoenig@bloomberg.net  